tellraw @p \
{text: "How to Enchant items using Engine", bold:true, color: "aqua"}
tellraw @p \
{text: "This system makes it possible to enchant any item with any enchantment! Ever seen Fire Aspect tridents?",color:white}

tellraw @p \
{text: ""}

tellraw @p \
{text: "Random Enchanting",color:"#e0beeb"}
tellraw @p \
{text: "- Put your item in the middle. It will get enchanted with the most basic enchants and you will spend 3 XP points. You need 3 levels for this. Won't work if already enchanted",color:gray}

tellraw @p \
{text: "Strong Random Enchanting",color:"#d080f5"}
tellraw @p \
{text: "- Put your item in the middle and surround it with lapis. It will get enchanted akin to 20-level graded enchantments. You need 3 levels for this. Won't work if already enchanted",color:gray}

tellraw @p \
{text: "Applying Enchantments",color:"#73eb8d"}
tellraw @p \
{text: "- Put your item in the left center, your book in the right center. Put your hammer between them. It will apply your enchantment onto your item. You need 15 levels for this. Can apply illegal enchantment combos. Can't apply if the item has more than 3 enchantments already",color:gray}

tellraw @p \
{text: "Transferring Enchantments",color:"#73eb8d"}
tellraw @p \
{text: "- Put your source item in the left center, your target item in the right center. Put your hammer between them. It will transfer enchantments from the source item to the target item.. You need 10 levels for this. Clears enchantments from source",color:gray}

tellraw @p \
{text: "Removing Enchantments",color:"#eb8173"}
tellraw @p \
{text: "- Put your item in the bottom middle. It will get unenchanted and you'll receive 1 XP point",color:gray}
